# Privacy Policy – ChoroyApp

Last updated: March 2025

ChoroyApp respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data.

## Information We Collect
ChoroyApp may collect the following information:
- User account information (such as email or username)
- App usage data for performance and debugging purposes
- Images or media selected by the user (only when explicitly requested)

## Camera Permission
ChoroyApp may request access to the device camera solely for features that allow users to capture or upload images.
Camera access is **only used when the user explicitly initiates an action** that requires it.
No images or videos are captured or transmitted without user consent.

## Data Storage
- Relational data is stored securely in PostgreSQL.
- Non-relational data is stored in MongoDB.
- Logs and diagnostics are handled by a separate logging service.

## Data Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or rent users’ personal data to third parties.

## Security
We apply industry-standard security practices to protect user data.

## Changes
This privacy policy may be updated from time to time.

## Contact
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
**contact@choroyapp.com**
